From aefbb22bdf05e654b29dfb779490d40e8c859900 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "F.Liu" <1661888967@qq.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 21:06:14 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] feat(ascend): add layerwise KV cache reuse support

Build layer reuse on top of the layerwise KV pool (#10077): multiple
layers time-multiplex a single shared transfer buffer, lowering HBM
footprint. num_blocks is kept whole by inflating the reported available
memory; the model runner then merges per-layer KVCacheTensor entries into
shared buffers (shared_by).

- layerwise_config.py: parse num_shared_buffers / prefetch_layers /
  independent_layers from kv_connector_extra_config and compute the shared
  storage slot layout (get_layerwise_storage_indices /
  get_layerwise_kv_cache_num_tensors).
- worker.py: inflate the reported available memory by total_layers /
  num_tensors (independent + shared buffers) so vLLM sizes num_blocks for
  the full layer count without over-allocating.
- model_runner_v1.py: merge per-layer KVCacheTensor entries into shared
  buffers and reject hybrid attention+mamba reuse.
- pool_worker / pool_scheduler: drive prefetch/offload from LayerwiseConfig.
  Per-layer load range splits by buffer ownership (gated by has_layer_reuse,
  so non-reuse keeps the standard start block): independent layers load
  only the blocks the pool has beyond HBM (dedicated buffer keeps
  HBM-cached KV valid), while shared (time-multiplexed) layers reload every
  block from block 0 since HBM hits are not reliable. Load shared metadata
  is built per distinct block-range shape so the split is not flattened
  back onto all layers.

Signed-off-by: F.Liu <1661888967@qq.com>
