From 7968b8009bf9ea4601bdde003482791b5317527d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "F.Liu" <1661888967@qq.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 01:37:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] fix(kv_pool): free blocks immediately on request finish
 in layerwise mode

AscendStoreConnector is SupportsHMA, so vLLM invokes
request_finished_all_groups (not request_finished). The HMA path missed
the layerwise early-return present in request_finished, so a layerwise
producer with saved tokens returned delay_free_blocks=True. vLLM then
deferred the free, but layerwise never records a sending event (only
touch_sending_mamba_blocks does), so update_connector_output never freed
those blocks -- GPU KV cache usage climbed monotonically to 100%.

Add the same `if self.use_layerwise: return False` guard so blocks are
freed immediately on request finish. This is safe because layerwise saves
each layer synchronously before the request finishes (save_kv_layer waits
on the last layer's save event).

Signed-off-by: F.Liu <1661888967@qq.com>
---
 .../kv_transfer/kv_pool/ascend_store/pool_scheduler.py    | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vllm_ascend/distributed/kv_transfer/kv_pool/ascend_store/pool_scheduler.py b/vllm_ascend/distributed/kv_transfer/kv_pool/ascend_store/pool_scheduler.py
index 9c363538f21..8c7efc0cda5 100644
--- a/vllm_ascend/distributed/kv_transfer/kv_pool/ascend_store/pool_scheduler.py
+++ b/vllm_ascend/distributed/kv_transfer/kv_pool/ascend_store/pool_scheduler.py
@@ -1041,6 +1041,14 @@ def request_finished_all_groups(
         if self.kv_role == "kv_consumer" and not self.consumer_is_to_put:
             self._delayed_free_req_ids.discard(request.request_id)
             return False, None
+        if self.use_layerwise:
+            # Layerwise saves each layer synchronously before the request
+            # finishes (save_kv_layer waits on the last layer's save event),
+            # so blocks can be freed immediately. Delaying them here would
+            # leak: layerwise never records a sending event, so
+            # update_connector_output would never free these blocks.
+            self._delayed_free_req_ids.discard(request.request_id)
+            return False, None
         tracker = self._request_trackers.get(request.request_id)
         if tracker is not None and tracker.num_saved_tokens <= 0:
             self._delayed_free_req_ids.discard(request.request_id)

From fd6cee275c19a57ab3954fa0ddff5c435a5a30d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "F.Liu" <1661888967@qq.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 16:32:37 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] feat(kv_pool): sync ascend_store save with mooncake PD
 transfer per layer

When ascend_store layer-reuse and mooncake PD-disaggregation coexist on a
prefill node (AscendMultiConnector), both read the same per-layer KV
buffer. Without synchronization the ascend_store save thread can mark a
layer done (letting the next layer overwrite the time-multiplexed buffer)
before mooncake finishes sending that layer's KV to the decode node,
corrupting the PD transfer.

Port the per-layer `layer_transfer_finished_events` mechanism from
prefill_offload_0604:
- pool_worker: create per-layer events on a prefill node
  (use_gva_layerwise + layerwise_offload + kv_role in kv_both/kv_producer)
  and publish them via a module global (get_shared_layer_transfer_events).
- kv_transfer: the save thread waits for the mooncake PD event (after
  batch_copy, before set layer_save_finished) so a layer is only marked
  saved after its PD transfer finished. All ops are None-guarded.
- mooncake_layerwise_connector: the send thread asserts the event is
  clear before transfer and sets it after the layer's PD transfer
  finishes; register_kv_caches pulls the shared events via the getter.

Unlike prefill_offload_0604 (kv_both only), the creation condition is
broadened to kv_producer so it actually triggers on PD-disaggregated
prefill nodes.

Signed-off-by: F.Liu <1661888967@qq.com>
