From 8dfc5ee3c7f03e5d0f0bb52f497e04938433a0e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "F.Liu" <1661888967@qq.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 20:42:20 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] fix(kv_pool): re-land #10077 base modules for
 layerwise-with-reuse

feature/layerwise-kv-pool-with-reuse was rebased onto a99b3b26, where #10077
had been reverted (PR #11021). The reuse commits only touch pool_scheduler/
pool_worker/kv_transfer/mooncake_layerwise_connector/layerwise_config/
model_runner/worker, so the reverted base modules they depend on were left
missing or gutted, breaking imports (memcache_comm_fence deleted,
backend/__init__ emptied of backend_map, config_data stripped of layerwise
fields).

Restore those base modules from feature/layerwise-kv-pool (PR #11104), whose
correctly main-merged versions keep both the layerwise and mamba field sets:
- memcache_comm_fence.py (deleted by revert; pool_worker imports its gates)
- backend/__init__.py (restore backend_map and exports)
- backend/{backend,memcache_backend,mooncake_backend}.py
- config_data.py (RequestTracker keeps layerwise + mamba fields; mamba fields
  default to None/0 so #10077-style construction stays compatible)
- ascend_store_connector.py

Verified: all 14 touched files py_compile; 159/159 internal import names
resolve; ruff check passes. Unit tests require torch/vllm/torch_npu (NPU).

Signed-off-by: F.Liu <1661888967@qq.com>
